name: InfluenzaVaccineAdministrationICD9CM
title: Influenza Vaccine Administration ICD9CM
description: Developed by OFMQ for Immunization measures
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values identifies patients who are administered the influenza vaccination.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to represent the procedure of administering the influenza vaccine.  Using the Quality Data Model, this data element maps to the Procedure category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only include codes which represent the procedure of administering a vaccine.  Codes used are to be ICD9 codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.)
